EmailTemplate.description: When R&S notifies of AL settlement rejection, AP to advise AL & ask for new BM
EmailTemplate.name: Notifying AL of settlement rejection
EmailTemplate.subject: Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber} - {!Case.Subject}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear Participant,
We were notified by our Remittance & Settlement team that the last settlement for the airline in BSP/CASS {!Case.Country__c} was rejected due to "to insert the reason as per R&S advise"
As per our records, the airlines Bank details are as below;
Beneficiary Name: As per IRIS
Bank A/C #: eg, 1234XXXXXXXXXXXX12
BIC/SWIFT Code: as per IRIS
Please reconfirm the above details with your bank and note, for settlement purposes it is mandatory for the airline to provide IATA with a valid Banking Mandate.
- The mandate can be provided in two forms: Local bank account in the CASS Country and Currency or IATA Currency Clearance Service (ICCS) contract for cross border payments instructions
- For more information on ICCS please visit http://www.iata.org/services/finance/iccs/Pages/index.aspx<http://www.iata.org/service/finance/iccs/Pages/index.aspx>
- If you would like to use a local bank account, please note that the corresponding mandate must be issued as per the attached instructions and template, and signed at your Airline Head Office by two senior officers. At least one of which must be:
o Chief Financial Officer (CFO) or
o Head of Treasury or Head of Cash Management Department
We seek your prompt action in sending us new Banking Instructions to avoid any hassles with regards to the airlines participation.
Your urgent & prompt response to this email is requested & will be appreciated.
Thank you & Best regards,
{!Case.OwnerFullName}
Global Airline Participation Team
Financial and Distribution Services
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
www.iata.org/customer
